Kuni Tyessi in Abuja The Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board (JAMB) will commence the sale of 2022 Unified Tertiary Matriculation Examination (UTME) and Direct Entry (DE) application forms on February 12, 2022. JAMB Director of Public Relations, Dr. Fabian Benjamin, disclosed this in the Board’s weekly bulletin released in Abuja yesterday. It announced that the “UTME/DE registration will start on February 12, 2022, and end on March 19, 2022, while mock examination will be held on April 20, 2022, and UTME from April 20 to 30, 2022.” In a related development, the Board is set to refund N4,000 each to candidates who had deposited a draft of N4,000 for late registration for the 2021 UTME and Direct Entry (DE) but were unable to complete the registration process owing to no fault of the Board. It urged the affected students to visit the Board’s website at https://www.jamb.gov.ng, and complete a form for the refund of the value of the draft they submitted to the Board. It stated: “The above candidates are to click on the link on the 2021 UTME/DE unregistered candidates bank draft recapture and fill the spaces, after which they would key in the token sent to the phone numbers they had presented during the submission of their drafts. “The token would be used to access a form on which they will fill in their account details for the refund of the value of the draft.”